   "body" : "Trying to compile this from source and I'm hitting this error with\r\n\r\n```\r\n.rodata' can not be used when making a shared object; recompile with -fPIC\r\nlibbitcoin_consensus.a: error adding symbols: Bad value\r\n```\r\nI run the `./configure --with-incompatible-bdb` and it doesn't have any errors, and I use that `--with-incompatible-bdb` because I have Berkeley DB 5.3, which is higher than the recommended 4.8 version, and it's so much hassle trying to get the previous packages without breaking my linux install.\r\n\r\nbut anyway I'm not sure what I might be missing which is causing the said error above when I run the `make check` command which produces the following in the error output in Terminal;\r\n\r\n```\r\n  CXXLD    bitcoind\r\n/usr/bin/ld: libbitcoin_consensus.a(libbitcoin_consensus_a-cryptonight.o): relocation R_X86_64_32S against `.rodata' can not be used when making a shared object; recompile with -fPIC\r\nlibbitcoin_consensus.a: error adding symbols: Bad value\r\ncollect2: error: ld returned 1 exit status\r\nMakefile:3714: recipe for target 'bitcoind' failed\r\nmake[2]: *** [bitcoind] Error 1\r\n\r\n```",
